annotation.TEXT: Oh, there's a 1-up that Ninja Boy never found, since he didn't turn around to check the lower route here.
So, this hack is by Brad172, and the reason I'm playing this is because Ninja Boy tried to LP it, but the music broke on his more accurate emulator.
Ha, there's no notice telling me not to harm the wildlife here!
I kicked that shell at such a high velocity that those shell-less yellow Koopas couldn't hop over it in time. Anyway, there's Yoshi coin #5.
Oh, well. I'll at least hold onto the Fire Flower for later use, as I typically do.
Up next is Mushroom Woods.
Bonus game average: 4 / 1 = 4 1-ups each.
BGM: Mega Man 2 - Wood Man's Stage (partial)
Add a comma after "Mario" here.
I bet it was whatever's causing the echo in the music here. However, the game didn't completely break for Ninja Boy here, as the sound effects still worked for him.
So, he rewound back to before he got the star and played through the level again without it.
Awesome, that was the fifth Yoshi coin.
Goal tape average: 130 / 3 = 43.333 stars each.
50-star goal tape hits: 1 Goal tape average: 90 / 2 = 45 stars each.
So, yeah. This hack's level design is broken just like that... or is it? Well, we'll see...
Okay, and now for Mushroom Pass.
Mushroom Mountains, eh? Well, here we go!
Okay, now over here, less than 20 seconds into the first real level, we find our first chance to get a cape.
However, I still primarily use the less accurate ZSNES, where this hack's music doesn't break, so I decided to give this a go.
BGM: Pikmin - Forest Navel
Also, I think this is an incomplete port of Wood Man Stage's theme...
Okay, let's see if I missed anything of value in the sky around here.
Oh, yeah. I still have to check out the rest of the broken bridge below.
Doesn't look like anything of interest at all.
There are bullet cannons down here... which don't fire...?
Hmm... Ninja Boy didn't check out what's down there. Let's take a look...
Oh, BTW, this level did actually play its music on Ninja Boy's emulator without breaking at all.
Okay, now for Ninja Boy, this music only played like the first note before breaking. (And yet, Mark D was able to successfully identify this music from that one note!)
BTW, SMW Central states that this hack has 21 exits. (Ninja Boy only got through 4 levels before the breaking music caused an unavoidable crash on him.)
Nope. Well, you never know, especially since this hack allowed the player access to a cape so quickly.
That Yoshi coin clearly required flying to reach.
Alright, I believe I'll end it off here for today. Next time, I'll play the level that crashed the game on Ninja Boy's emulator, and then take on some brand new stuff...
Alright, here's the goal, and I managed to avoid killing anything in this level, even despite the huge temptation to go on a rampage for a killer combo.
Pfft... That was silly.
Oh, let me erase that "0" file from when I was testing to hear what the custom music sounded like on ZSNES.
To be continued... Yo!
Yes, I have to see Yoshi immediately, if not sooner! Oh, and of course Bowser's made new traps. Did you expect him to keep reusing his old traps or something?
Okay, I'll try not to harm anything in this level from this point forward.
Whoa, almost screwed up on that Paragoomba.
Silly sound effect FTW.
Haha, I bet that Koopa didn't see that coming.
Hello, and welcome to...
BGM: Mega Man 9 - Thunder Tornado
The music here was vanilla, so I did the obvious thing in editing.
Oh, whoops! Sorry, Wiggler! It's just a little bump on the head! I'm sure you'll recover!
Wow, the accuracy on that cape-flight stomp there.
Push!
64 is an awesome number.
HARRY UP!
I wonder why this little pond is here... Anyway, there's the goal. I'll use my cape to aim for a high goal tape amount.
Alright, now to take a swim across the map to reach the next level.
Ooh, good thing I went back to check up here, or I would've missed that Yoshi coin.
Okay, so this level tells you not to harm the wildlife, and then tries really hard to tempt you into going on a rampage with this star.
BGM: Keitai Denjuu Telefang - Wild Denjuu Battle
Alright, I have access to either Yoshi's... Er, Mario's House or Mushroom Pass to begin with. Let's start with Mario's House here.
Just gotta check to see if there's anything in the upper-left.
And, of course, erase it a total of eight times just to be absolutely sure.
Gotta check every pipe...
Okay, now this is another song that broke for Ninja Boy right away, although the sound effects remained for him again, indicating that the game wouldn't crash.
...Yoshi's Emergency!
And then, just after I say that, I switch back to the cape, although it was so I could unnecessarily glide across that pit.
BGM: Super Mario 64 - Wing/Vanish Caps
Uh, oh. Vanilla "Here We Go!" music. I'd better not stay here for very long. Also, the sign under the mailbox still says "Yoshi".
And now for a "blind" bonus game!
Oh, there's another 1-up that Ninja Boy missed. (Always take a peek behind where you start a level, just in case there's something there.)
Oh, never mind. They do. The first two didn't, but maybe that was just due to the timing of them first appearing, and when I was briefly standing on them.
Alright, that's it for the title demo, so let's start the game!
I can totally make this jump without needing the springboard, once this Wiggler moves out of the way. Of course, this means I'll be bringing the springboard with me.
There's the midpoint, and I bet this pipe is where I'd emerge when starting this level from the midway entrance.
That P-switch does little aside from making this bridge safer to cross.
Oh, there's my first Fire Flower, not counting the roulette item near the start. I'll try to use the Fire Flower more often than the cape for the most part.
Seems like having a cape available so early was intentional. Okay, I'll go ahead and fly at first, but then I'll turn around and show the broken bridge below.
Nothing in the air that way.
Speaking of the star, its music completely broke for Ninja Boy, taking the sound effects with it, and resulting in the game locking up when he finished the level.
There's unreachable munchers down there. I guess they're just for decoration.
Oh, I can easily aim for the top of this goal without a cape, so I'll switch to my flower now.
Well, hot diggity! It seems karma has rewarded my pacifism with a 50 here!
Aww... Perfect rhythm, but just didn't match the center tile again. I will one day...
Goal tape average: 40 / 1 = 40 stars each.
And now to go back.
Yeah, yeah. I'm near the end of the level.
